# How to change the port
# ======================
#
# The Tardiness Check server defaults to port 3000.
# To use a different port, edit THIS FILE and put just the port number.
# Example: change 3000 to 8080 to make the server run on http://localhost:8080
#
# After editing this file:
#   1. Stop the server (Ctrl+C in the Start.bat window)
#   2. Double-click Start.bat again
#   3. The browser will open on the new port
#
# Alternative: set the PORT environment variable before running Start.bat
# Example (in a terminal):  set PORT=8080  (then run Start.bat)
#
# Why change the port?
#   - Another app on your school PC is using port 3000
#   - Your IT department requires a specific port
#   - You're running multiple instances
#
3000
